					About
				
			

			

				
					

	If you have the license for Oracle Diagnostic Pack, then J-Tools can be used to display diagnostics data for the Oracle database. 
	Enable the check-box for help on Database menu-tab to get tool-tips.

					Requirements
				
			

			

				

						  Client:
    
							
  • Windows 7/8
    • 
							
  • Internet Explorer 11 32-bit with Activex enabled and upto 1 GB of RAM available to be utilized by J-Tools
    • 
							
  • Oracle 11g/12c 32-bit ODBC driver
    • 
						  
			   						
						  Server:
    
							
  • Oracle 11g/12c Database with Diagnostics Pack enabled
    • 
						  
			   						
						  User:
    
							
  • Access to "DBA_*" views & "GV$*" views, which are relevant to Oracle AWR and session information.
    • 
						  
			   						
						
			

			

				
					Known Issues
				
			

			

				
					  
    
						
  • #BG000001: Using the charts continuously on pages like "Active Session History" leaks memory.
    • 
					  
			   						
						
			

			

				
					Known Limitations
				
			

			

				
					  
    
						
  • #LM000001: Some of the data-types like "XMLType", Raw etc are not supported.
    •
